					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Pretty much this. It says in the article, estimated numbers are a 1000 people per year. Turns out a LOT of people get struck by lightning, and a lot of it probably never even gets reported, so it's close to impossible to definitively get every single case.</p> 
				 	]]>
